    "visualHierarchy": "Visual hierarchy is established through clear visual separation between notification items, using dividers. Titles are given prominence with a larger font size, and secondary details (description and timestamp) use smaller font sizes.",
    "variantSelectionRationale": "For the list-item component, I chose 'Condition=2-line' to accommodate the notification title and description. 'Leading=Image' and 'Trailing=None' were selected to include the user avatar while omitting any unnecessary trailing elements.  I rejected the other 'Condition' options as they are not needed, and 'Leading' and 'Trailing' were simplified for mobile constraints."
